POLIOMYELITIS UPDATE (22): WPV1 ACUTE FLACCID PARALYSIS PAKISTAN (KHYBER PAKHTUNKHWA)
*************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 27 May 2022
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/pakistan-reports-5th-and-6th-wild-poliovirus-cases-in-north-waziristan-children-76642/


Pakistan officials report 2 more confirmed wild polio cases from North Waziristan, leaving a young boy and a girl paralyzed. Both children are 18 months old and belong to Mir Ali. The female child had onset of paralysis on 10 May 2022 and the male child on 11 May 2022.

Both cases were confirmed by the Pakistan National Polio Laboratory at the National Institute of Health, Islamabad on Thursday [26 May 2022]. This is the 5th and 6th cases in North Waziristan, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, this year [2022].

"These children will struggle for the rest of their lives because of the pain of disabilities caused by polio. I urge the people of Pakistan to vaccinate your children," said Federal Health Minister Abdul Qadir Patel.

The southern districts of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa that include North and South Waziristan, DI Khan, Bannu, Tank and Lakki Marwat, are at highest risk of wild poliovirus. While no human transmission has been reported outside North Waziristan, 2 positive environmental samples were reported from Bannu between April and May [2022].

"All children suffering from wild polio are being offered rehabilitation services, but regardless of the support the government provides, there is [no] cure to polio. The only way to protect children is to give them repeated doses of the polio vaccine," said Federal Health Secretary Aamir Ashraf Khawaja.

All children confirmed with wild polio this year [2022] belong to North Waziristan, where more cases are expected due to high refusal rates and instances of finger-marking without vaccination during campaigns.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[Clearly the WPV1 has found a significant-sized pool of unvaccinated susceptible persons in North Waziristan. There are now 6 cases in this area plus the one case in Afghanistan reported with onset in 2022, bringing the total cases to date this year (2022) to 7, one more than reported in 2021. As the media report says, more cases are expected.

A map of Pakistan with districts can be found at https://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/pak215_pakistan_districts_v5_a0_20181203.pdf. - Mod.MPP

